            <div facs="ht:chi.12945678&amp;view=1up&amp;seq=627" type="entry">
                <p><label type="entry">VELARIUS</label>, an officer in the court of the Roman
                    emperors, being a kind of usher, whose post was behind the curtain in the
                    prince’s apartment, as that of the chancellor’s was at the entry of the
                    ballustrade, and that of the ostiarii at the door. The velarii had a superior of
                    the same denomination, who commanded them.</p>
